    {
      "id": "jd_root",
      "type": "class",
      "label": "JobDescription",
      "description": "Job Description document",
      "position": {
        "x": -239.15566749363552,
        "y": 306.3744684710171
      },
      "semantics": "OUTPUT FORMAT: Plain text only. No markdown. No # ## ### headings \u2014 use ALL CAPS for section titles instead. No **bold** or *italic* \u2014 use plain words. No --- dividers. No numbered lists. When a list is needed, always use \"- \" dash prefix. No * bullets.\n\nGENERATION CONTRACT \u2014 follow this exactly when generating a document from this ontology.\n\nSECTION ORDER: Generate sections in this order, using only non-:context dimension clusters: About the Company, The Role, Who We're Looking For, What You'll Be Doing, Technical Requirements, Compensation & Benefits.\n\nTAG RULES:\n- [:context] = background knowledge only \u2014 inform tone/style but do NOT create a section or heading for it\n- [:list] = generate as a 1-sentence intro followed by a bullet list of specific items. No prose paragraphs.\n- [:paragraph] = flowing prose only, no sub-headings, no bullet points\n- [:short] = 2\u20133 short paragraphs maximum, no sub-headings\n- [:single-paragraph] = exactly 1 paragraph, no sub-headings, no bullets \u2014 weave all attributes inline\n- [:salary-line] = bold salary range on its own line, then 2\u20133 short benefit bullets. No sub-headings.\n\nCOVERAGE GOAL: Reference at least 70% of non-:context nodes by their label in the output.\n\nNEVER GENERATE:\n- \"What you'll own\" as a section heading\n- \"Domain Knowledge\" as a section heading\n- \"Functional Domain\" as a section heading\n- \"How to Apply\" or \"Apply\" section\n- \"Why This Role\" or \"Why Now\" section\n- \"Equity Structure\" as a section heading\n- \"Career Progression\" as a section heading\n- \"How We Communicate\" section\n- \"Interview Process\" section\n- Equal opportunity / EEO boilerplate\n- Horizontal rules (---) as dividers\n\nDIMENSION MAP: After the main response, append a <dimension_map> JSON block mapping ontology clusters to values used in your response:\n<dimension_map>\n{\"CLUSTER_NAME\": {\"property_key\": \"value from response\"}}\n</dimension_map>",
      "examples": [
        "Senior ML Engineer at Series B startup",
        "Entry-level Marketing Analyst at enterprise"
      ],
      "constraints": [
        "role_family required",
        "seniority_level required"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "version": "2.0",
        "total_dimensions": "43",
        "onet_aligned": "true"
      }
    },
